cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.CC

This paper deals with measuring and computing database inconsistency, which is a topic closely related to database management systems (cs.DB). The use of answer-set programs to compute the proposed measure suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of repair semantics is related to logic (cs.LO), and the paper also discusses mechanisms for computing the measure, which could be seen as a software engineering (cs.SE) problem. Finally, the use of numerical measures and computations suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC).
